Clean the bottle using hot soapy water and be sure you rinse well. To remove the label, soak bottles in the large pot. Bring water to a boil and then submerge bottles and allow them to sit in the boiling water. Once water comes to a rolling boil, turn off heat and allow bottles to cool slightly. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/bb\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/bb\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Peel label while holding the bottle by the neck with your potholder. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/99\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/99\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Dry bottle well. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/ca\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/ca\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Find an along the bottle base to make your cut. The bottle cutter will score the bottle. Use a water hose clamp as guide. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/1b\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/1b\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Put firm pressure on the bottle as you make your cut. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/63\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/63\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Bottle cutter will score the bottle and not cut all the way through the glass. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/ba\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/ba\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Have the tub of ice water waiting so you can make an instant transfer. The bottle will make a “pop” sound as it separates. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0e\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0e\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":331,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":547.032967032967,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Wiggle bottle halves apart and place top half aside. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/ce\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/ce\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":326,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":538.6813186813187,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Dry tumbler half.

Place your sandpaper on a hard, flat surface (a kitchen counter would work well) and rub the tumbler mouth over the paper. Use consistent pressure but don’t press too hard. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6b\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6b\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":346,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":571.0439560439561,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Buff edges to create a smooth rim. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/bd\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/bd\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":343,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":566.8681318681319,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Wipe edges with rag as you sand to evaluate areas that need sanding or are in good shape. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/3\/3d\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/3\/3d\/Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Turn-Wine-Bottles-Into-Wine-Tumblers-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

